column5: I dabble in it Bill. :-)
Roy, I only dabbled when I had to   I think grade 4 and grade 9? lol
Duude you're like the Yoda of funky camera angles!!  Thanks dawg.
And he called me Fido!!  Something I havnt been called since what, grade 6?!
nice fish!
Good job Castro!
Well you coulda called     Then you wouldn't have been out there all lonesome  Very nice fish Fidel  Joey
Oh Joey... darling..  what a tangled web we weeve..  Think Paul would mind if we went on a little steelie date?!  Thanks sug!
I'm thinking you owe an apology.  Hmmmmmmmmm...........................................         April buddy.  I promise
Well fidel I should ov went with ya that morn, now im wallowing in my crapulance.  Good times good times  Andy
I bet you were speaking Francais when you fell in

Had an itch Friday night... You know the one!!  Crepped into the rivah before first light and stayed off the beaten path.  My calf muscles are still taught from all the wading..  She was fast, but gin clear..  STELLAR!!  What a day..  Almost every pool, pocket, run, and seam held fish..  Caught my fill, lost some HAWGS too.  Must remember to go heavier on the tipet.  Enjoy!!          cheers everybody!  H to the Dizzow.  Solo budday... we're waiting!!
WTG brah!!
That trib looks really familiar......The one I'm thinking of is closed to fishing??? Hmmmmmmmmm..........................................
And which one would that be?
Awesome buddy!!  Uh oh, now that you've posted those pic's with backgrounds clearly visible that river is doomed!  So did you get 'em on the fly?
I could be wrong, its been known to happen once before! lol lol Looks alot like B Creek? NO?
No not Bronte.
i thought the exact same thing minnow, i seen the pics then read the posts and so did you, anyway nice fish bud
Good job Fidel!!!!  I went for a swim yesterday   It was cold to say the least.
Great report and pics HD  Looks like you were able to satisfy that itch of yours!!!   Beautiful chrome    Congratulations  Merci de partager cette belle journ√©e avec nous mon ami!!! Jacques
Thanks bud.  Nah, I was chucking and ducking...  There was a couple guys swinging spey flies, but the water is still a tad cold for working bigger stuff IMO.  I just wanted to get my fill!!
If ya woulda shot me a pm, I woulda gabbed a little...  Now I don't wanna!!
Aye merci!!  J'essaye...
OOOHH!  Had a little polar dunk did ya?!  Wha happen?
Nice Steelies HD...that first male is quite the hog !!! .... Today was a stellar day out there indeed. Good to see you got into some fish after that hit and miss with the boys....
Thanks brotha.  I made him look bigger than he is.. teheh
Great Report!  Nice Pics.
Great fish you got there HD....thanks for sharing.
Steve's mad you used the word epic to describe your report.  He said it... I'm just the messenger.  I thought, OK... epic enough report for me.  Nice going.
Great reportage Fidel.  Thanks for sharing
That river IS doomed, because I'm going there tomorrow with other eminent anglers from this board, and we gonna clean her OUT!    p.-  p.s. bravo fidel, tu me bottes le c u l !
LOL Too funny...  Wish I could go with ya bud.  Take your time when you cross the river though..  She's extremely fast.
Good to see you got out and terrorized the skinny water Salmoonoids Feedell!!!   I suspected some camera angle enhancement in the first pic!  ... not that there's anything wrong with that.
Un calvaire de beau rapport Fido!
Je nais parle pas francias!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
